column1: For every Emergency Department encounter, hospitals (licensed by the California Department of Public Health) may report a Principal Procedure and up to 20 Other Procedures.  The Procedure Code Frequency Report shows the frequency of the reporting of each code.
ProcedureCode = the procedure code, according to CPT-4 (Current Procedural Terminology, Fourth Edition).
TotalProc = the total number of times the procedure code was reported in a Principal or Other Procedure position.
PrimaryProc = the total number of times the procedure code was reported as a Principal Procedure.
SecondaryProc = the total number of times the procedure code was reported in one of the Other Procedure positions.
Data Source: California Emergency Department Data, Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development
